---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";

const lastUpdated = "July 10, 2026";
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy | Glimt"
  description="Privacy policy for the Glimt mobile application."
  noindex={true}
>
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-8">
        <div>
          <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-heading font-bold text-bark">
            Privacy Policy
          </h1>
          <p class="text-sm text-bark/50">Glimt</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-sm text-bark/40 mb-8">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <div class="prose-article">
        <p>
          This privacy policy applies to <strong>Glimt</strong>, the couples
          conversation app published by Fjord Labs (the “App”). Glimt is built
          to be private by design: your conversations happen between you and
          your partner, off the screen. We do not sell, rent, or share your
          personal information with advertisers or third-party marketers, and
          we collect only what the App needs to work.
        </p>

        <h2>Works Without an Account</h2>

        <p>
          You can use all of Glimt without creating an account. In that case
          your favorites, deck progress, streak, and settings are stored only
          on your device and never leave it. The question decks themselves are
          bundled inside the App, so it works fully offline.
        </p>

        <h2>What We Collect (only if you sign in)</h2>

        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Account information.</strong> When you sign in, we store
            the account identifier provided by your chosen sign-in method
            (email address, Apple Sign In, or Google). Authentication is
            handled securely through Supabase.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Your backup.</strong> Signing in backs up your favorites,
            deck progress, and streak so you can restore them on a new device.
            We never store your answers or conversations — the App doesn't
            record them at all.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          We do <strong>not</strong> collect data for advertising, tracking,
          or profiling, and the App contains no analytics SDKs.
        </p>

        <h2>Shared Account Across Fjord Apps</h2>

        <p>
          Glimt uses the shared Fjord Apps authentication system, so one
          account signs you in to any of our apps. Your account identity is
          shared across the apps, but your Glimt data is used only to operate
          Glimt for you.
        </p>

        <h2>Purchases</h2>

        <p>
          Glimt Premium is a monthly or annual subscription. Payments are
          processed entirely by Apple; we never see your payment details. We
          use RevenueCat to associate your subscription with your account so
          it can be restored on any device.
        </p>

        <h2>Notifications</h2>

        <p>
          The optional daily reminder is a local notification scheduled on
          your device. It requires your permission, never leaves your phone,
          and can be turned off anytime in Settings.
        </p>

        <h2>Data Storage and Security</h2>

        <p>
          Backup data is stored using Supabase, which provides secure,
          industry-standard infrastructure for authentication and database
          storage. Access controls ensure only your account can read and
          write your data.
        </p>

        <h2>Data Retention and Deletion</h2>

        <p>
          We keep your backup for as long as you maintain an account. You can
          delete all of your Glimt data at any time from within the App
          (Settings → Delete account &amp; data) — this permanently removes
          your favorites, progress, and streak from our servers. Because one
          Fjord account works across all our apps, the shared sign-in identity
          itself is kept so your other Fjord apps keep working; if you would
          like the shared account erased entirely, email us and we will remove
          it.
        </p>

        <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>

        <p>
          The App is intended for people in a relationship and is rated 12+.
          It is not directed at children under the age of 13, and we do not
          knowingly collect personal information from children.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>

        <p>
          We may update this privacy policy from time to time. When we do, we
          will revise the “Last updated” date at the top of this page.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>

        <p>
          Questions about this policy? Email
          <a href="mailto:fjordlabs.app@gmail.com">fjordlabs.app@gmail.com</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
